00:59:38.100 --> 00:59:39.750
It's a religious marker.

00:59:39.750 --> 00:59:44.100
It can't be publicly visible,
but it can be a public issue.

00:59:44.100 --> 00:59:50.220
When there was a medical
problem in a case in Cologne,

00:59:50.220 --> 00:59:56.800
in Germany now,
and it was in 2010,

00:59:56.800 --> 00:59:59.540
and it became a very
important debate,

00:59:59.540 --> 01:00:01.820
and the court,
regional court, decided

01:00:01.820 --> 01:00:07.890
to forbid the circumcision
of young boys,

01:00:07.890 --> 01:00:12.090
with the argument that it is the
violation of physical integrity

01:00:12.090 --> 01:00:13.950
of the young boys.

01:00:13.950 --> 01:00:16.210
Of course, well, this
is the irony of history.

01:00:16.210 --> 01:00:18.900
It's quite sad, but
Germany, who has

01:00:18.900 --> 01:00:23.940
done so important work
in relation to the past,

01:00:23.940 --> 01:00:26.470
that we haven't done in
other parts of the world,

01:00:26.470 --> 01:00:32.390
like in Turkey, so although they
have done this work of memory

01:00:32.390 --> 01:00:34.160
in relation to
Holocaust, they have just

01:00:34.160 --> 01:00:37.640
forgotten that circumcision
was a religious ritual that

01:00:37.640 --> 01:00:40.160
concerned Jewish
community as well.

01:00:40.160 --> 01:00:43.130
Of course, that triggered
a terrible anxiety

01:00:43.130 --> 01:00:45.470
within the Jewish community
because it was also

01:00:45.470 --> 01:00:50.240
framed as the most archaic
tradition that doesn't have

01:00:50.240 --> 01:00:52.550
its place in German society.

01:00:52.550 --> 01:00:56.540
And forbidding circumcision for
targeting Muslim population,

01:00:56.540 --> 01:01:00.320
mental, so, it brought in
the Jewish circumcision

01:01:00.320 --> 01:01:01.670
in the picture.

01:01:01.670 --> 01:01:06.650
So Jewish society, Jewish
community, reacted.

01:01:06.650 --> 01:01:10.970
They have transformed, with
the help of Merkel, the law.

01:01:10.970 --> 01:01:13.670
I don't go into details.

01:01:13.670 --> 01:01:16.460
But what is interesting
in that example,

01:01:16.460 --> 01:01:21.390
it's also belonging, because
is it a religious ritual?

01:01:21.390 --> 01:01:25.950
It is also a belonging
between a father and the son,

01:01:25.950 --> 01:01:29.910
because it's a way
of identification,

01:01:29.910 --> 01:01:34.620
both in Judaism and in Islam,
although there are differences,

01:01:34.620 --> 01:01:39.900
because it's not a Quranic
principle in the case of Islam,

01:01:39.900 --> 01:01:42.510
but it's an Abrahamic tradition.

01:01:42.510 --> 01:01:45.180
And it is a prophetic
tradition, so it

01:01:45.180 --> 01:01:48.750
became a custom, very
important custom,

01:01:48.750 --> 01:01:52.590
and it's a rite of
passage, rite of passage.

01:01:52.590 --> 01:01:54.600
So you belong to a
Muslim community,

01:01:54.600 --> 01:01:59.140
both for Muslim and Jewish male.

01:01:59.140 --> 01:02:01.910
It is a distinctive
trait of Muslim men.

01:02:01.910 --> 01:02:04.130
Of course, I know,
in the states,

01:02:04.130 --> 01:02:06.110
it has no such
distinctive trait.

01:02:06.110 --> 01:02:10.280
But in the past, and still,
it is an ongoing debate,

01:02:10.280 --> 01:02:14.930
circumcision as a kind of sense
of belonging within the family,

01:02:14.930 --> 01:02:17.000
but also it concerns women.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:21.830
Can women be married with
a non-circumcised man?

01:02:21.830 --> 01:02:24.890
So again, the
question of belonging

01:02:24.890 --> 01:02:30.250
