01:07:52.830 --> 01:07:54.890
- On the first
question, are you asking

01:07:54.890 --> 01:07:56.720
about the status of
Palestinian women

01:07:56.720 --> 01:07:59.640
in the occupied Palestinian
territory, specifically?

01:07:59.640 --> 01:08:02.674
Yeah, well, the law
that governs them

01:08:02.674 --> 01:08:04.340
depends on whether
they live in the West

01:08:04.340 --> 01:08:08.540
Bank in East Jerusalem, or
Gaza, because if they live--

01:08:08.540 --> 01:08:11.890
then they have
either British law

01:08:11.890 --> 01:08:13.700
that was in place
at the time, or they

01:08:13.700 --> 01:08:15.770
have Ottoman law that
was in place at the time,

01:08:15.770 --> 01:08:17.510
prior to the occupation.

01:08:17.510 --> 01:08:23.220
And these systems of
law, mostly penal code,

01:08:23.220 --> 01:08:25.250
but also family
law, have actually

01:08:25.250 --> 01:08:26.840
not been amended or updated.

01:08:26.840 --> 01:08:28.700
So they're actually
much more outdated

01:08:28.700 --> 01:08:30.669
than the laws in
Egypt or Morocco

01:08:30.669 --> 01:08:32.210
or other places
where there have been

01:08:32.210 --> 01:08:35.270
more regular updatings
of the family laws,

01:08:35.270 --> 01:08:37.380
and the penal
codes, and so forth.

01:08:37.380 --> 01:08:39.830
And so in many ways,
they retain many

01:08:39.830 --> 01:08:41.810
of the most regressive
features, one of which,

01:08:41.810 --> 01:08:43.700
for example, is the
'marry your rapist'

01:08:43.700 --> 01:08:48.800
provision that allows rapists
to marry their victims.

01:08:48.800 --> 01:08:51.439
And I should say that
most of these cases

01:08:51.439 --> 01:08:53.569
that we've seen of
marry your rapists, just

01:08:53.569 --> 01:08:57.470
to not terrify people,
are statutory rape cases,

01:08:57.470 --> 01:08:59.420
often boyfriend/girlfriend
cases,

01:08:59.420 --> 01:09:03.319
where technically it's rape,
and now the teenage daughter

01:09:03.319 --> 01:09:05.330
typically has been defiled.

01:09:05.330 --> 01:09:10.430
Then they want to marry
her off, and the boy

01:09:10.430 --> 01:09:13.160
can be prosecuted as a rapist.

01:09:13.160 --> 01:09:14.899
And so rather than
go to jail, they

01:09:14.899 --> 01:09:16.140
marry them off and so forth.

01:09:16.140 --> 01:09:19.609
But in other cases, it
actually is a 14-year-old girl

01:09:19.609 --> 01:09:21.560
forced to marry her
rapist because now, she's

01:09:21.560 --> 01:09:24.500
damaged goods and unwanted.

01:09:24.500 --> 01:09:27.170
And in fact, I remember
interviewing a young girl

01:09:27.170 --> 01:09:30.830
in Libya many years ago
who was in jail because she

01:09:30.830 --> 01:09:32.899
refused to marry her rapist.

01:09:32.899 --> 01:09:35.870
So there you have it.

01:09:35.870 --> 01:09:41.840
In other ways, there's a big
domestic violence problem,

01:09:41.840 --> 01:09:44.810
without a domestic violence law.

01:09:44.810 --> 01:09:47.330
And women do need
consent to marry,

01:09:47.330 --> 01:09:50.479
various other provisions
that are relics of these very

01:09:50.479 --> 01:09:52.124
outdated penal code systems.

01:09:52.124 --> 01:09:53.790
But one of the things
that's interesting

01:09:53.790 --> 01:09:55.670
and, whenever we've
taken on women's issues

01:09:55.670 --> 01:09:57.750
in the occupied
Palestinian territories,

01:09:57.750 --> 01:09:59.750
has taken a lot of
pushback, and sometimes it's

01:09:59.750 --> 01:10:03.320
very real, is that local
activists don't want

01:10:03.320 --> 01:10:05.420
to prioritize women's
issues because they say

01:10:05.420 --> 01:10:07.820
the occupation is the
number one issue in all

01:10:07.820 --> 01:10:09.604
of the ills of society--

01:10:09.604 --> 01:10:11.270
it's sort of a 'kick
your dog' syndrome.

01:10:11.270 --> 01:10:12.853
You're oppressed,
so you kick your dog

01:10:12.853 --> 01:10:14.440
or you kick your wife--

01:10:14.440 --> 01:10:17.340
are a result of the
occupation, and having

01:10:17.340 --> 01:10:19.150
to grapple with that.

01:10:19.150 --> 01:10:21.420
And in fact, there were
times when we actually

01:10:21.420 --> 01:10:24.420
had prepared a report on
domestic violence and spousal

01:10:24.420 --> 01:10:27.347
abuse, and so forth, and
we had to continually delay

01:10:27.347 --> 01:10:29.430
releasing the report because
there was another war

01:10:29.430 --> 01:10:30.390
and another conflict.

01:10:30.390 --> 01:10:33.520
And you can't drop a report
on domestic violence,

01:10:33.520 --> 01:10:36.810
whether in Egypt
or in Palestine,

01:10:36.810 --> 01:10:39.300
when people are being
slaughtered in the streets.

01:10:39.300 --> 01:10:41.850
And the dilemma that we always
have in the Middle East,

01:10:41.850 --> 01:10:46.980
now sadly in so many countries,
is that women's rights issues

01:10:46.980 --> 01:10:48.292
become de-prioritized.

01:10:48.292 --> 01:10:50.250
We had a major campaign
we were going to launch

01:10:50.250 --> 01:10:51.537
on child marriage in Yemen.

01:10:51.537 --> 01:10:53.620
There used to be a law
prohibiting child marriage.

01:10:53.620 --> 01:10:54.900
It was overturned.

01:10:54.900 --> 01:10:57.774
Mass epidemic of child
marriage in Yemen.

01:10:57.774 --> 01:10:59.940
And we just had to put it
on the cold burner because

01:10:59.940 --> 01:11:01.980
of this horrible war there.

01:11:01.980 --> 01:11:04.390
Nobody has the attention
span for these issues,

01:11:04.390 --> 01:11:07.206
or the capability
to address them.

01:11:07.206 --> 01:11:08.690
- And the LGBT issue?

01:11:08.690 --> 01:11:09.740
- Yeah, the LGBT issue.

01:11:09.740 --> 01:11:10.930
I'm glad you raised that.

01:11:10.930 --> 01:11:14.897
I mean, it's, in
ways, a women's issue.

01:11:14.897 --> 01:11:16.980
When I started at Human
Rights Watch 15 years ago,

01:11:16.980 --> 01:11:19.440
the unwritten rule
was, we don't talk

01:11:19.440 --> 01:11:21.290
about LGBT issues
in the Middle East

01:11:21.290 --> 01:11:23.290
unless it's through the
lens of another problem.

01:11:23.290 --> 01:11:25.500
So we wouldn't talk
about persecution

01:11:25.500 --> 01:11:27.180
of gays or lesbians.

01:11:27.180 --> 01:11:28.800
We would talk about torture.

01:11:28.800 --> 01:11:30.780
Oh, and by the
way, in this case,

01:11:30.780 --> 01:11:33.030
it's gay people who
are being tortured.

01:11:33.030 --> 01:11:35.820
Or police abuse,
oh, and by the way,

01:11:35.820 --> 01:11:39.060
it's transgender
women in Kuwait who

01:11:39.060 --> 01:11:42.990
are being burned and
assaulted by police.

01:11:42.990 --> 01:11:44.280
That's changed.

01:11:44.280 --> 01:11:46.470
That's changed a lot,
and we've taken our cues

01:11:46.470 --> 01:11:49.110
from the local LGBT
