01:23:50.730 --> 01:23:54.480
but the identity search
only can be possible

01:23:54.480 --> 01:23:58.650
if these people already are
mastering the languages,

01:23:58.650 --> 01:24:00.630
the communication codes.

01:24:00.630 --> 01:24:02.730
They're already
integrated into the system

01:24:02.730 --> 01:24:05.220
because otherwise,
it's not possible just

01:24:05.220 --> 01:24:06.330
to build up your identity.

01:24:06.330 --> 01:24:11.070
And identities in question
are always, not binary,

01:24:11.070 --> 01:24:15.430
but being hyphenated
identities, as we say,

01:24:15.430 --> 01:24:17.910
Latin-American or
Muslim-European.

01:24:17.910 --> 01:24:20.882
But this hyphen is
very complicated.

01:24:20.882 --> 01:24:21.840
That's what I'm saying.

01:24:21.840 --> 01:24:24.020
It's becoming more
and more complicated

01:24:24.020 --> 01:24:26.880
in the actual
political situation.

01:24:26.880 --> 01:24:28.910
Now that is related
with the second question

01:24:28.910 --> 01:24:30.140
I would like to go.

01:24:30.140 --> 01:24:32.330
It is not the
multicultural citizenship

01:24:32.330 --> 01:24:37.580
as a project that
really influences

01:24:37.580 --> 01:24:40.670
the political cultures of
the western democracies.

01:24:40.670 --> 01:24:44.390
On the contrary, we
shifted everywhere

01:24:44.390 --> 01:24:46.050
from the celebration
of minorities,

01:24:46.050 --> 01:24:50.000
of hyphenated
identities, to a kind

01:24:50.000 --> 01:24:52.700
of culture of majority making.

01:24:52.700 --> 01:24:55.130
And we were speaking
about cultural relativism,

01:24:55.130 --> 01:24:58.010
multiculturalism,
sometimes in critique

01:24:58.010 --> 01:24:59.180
of cultural relativism.

01:24:59.180 --> 01:25:02.240
Today, we speak of the
hierarchical values,

01:25:02.240 --> 01:25:05.450
so assimilation to an
American way of life,

01:25:05.450 --> 01:25:09.560
but the same even in very
liberal Great Britain,

01:25:09.560 --> 01:25:10.850
and the same in France.

01:25:10.850 --> 01:25:14.720
So identity issue is becoming
more and more, unfortunately,

01:25:14.720 --> 01:25:17.880
not the minorities,
but the majority

01:25:17.880 --> 01:25:20.630
making kind of instruments.

01:25:20.630 --> 01:25:25.670
So when French started to
discuss who are we as French,

01:25:25.670 --> 01:25:28.470
I started to be scared.

01:25:28.470 --> 01:25:30.030
And this is the kind of thing.

01:25:30.030 --> 01:25:31.760
And now we see,
although in France they

01:25:31.760 --> 01:25:35.070
didn't move into that
illiberal democracy.

01:25:35.070 --> 01:25:38.630
But in many places of Europe,
we see how illiberal democracies

01:25:38.630 --> 01:25:42.830
are growing, and I just
wanted to turn the gaze to us,

01:25:42.830 --> 01:25:49.340
and not to have always this
certitude, this, the certainty,

01:25:49.340 --> 01:25:50.870
in relation to women's rights.

01:25:50.870 --> 01:25:52.550
When we speak about
the Middle East,

01:25:52.550 --> 01:25:57.170
we always know what to do, but
when we look at the free women,

01:25:57.170 --> 01:25:59.300
and living in
Europe, and there it

01:25:59.300 --> 01:26:01.010
becomes much more
problematic when

01:26:01.010 --> 01:26:02.520
we turn the gaze to ourselves.

01:26:02.520 --> 01:26:05.060
So that's also what
I wanted to question.

01:26:05.060 --> 01:26:08.030
And in the case of maybe
international organizations,

01:26:08.030 --> 01:26:10.850
we need also
vernacular languages,

01:26:10.850 --> 01:26:14.660
rather than having one language
spreading from the west

01:26:14.660 --> 01:26:16.530
to the other parts of the world.

01:26:16.530 --> 01:26:20.030
I think it's inevitable,
maybe, but even LGBTI.

01:26:20.030 --> 01:26:25.891
Even knowing how to pronounce
it gives you some kind of power.

01:26:25.891 --> 01:26:26.390
OK.

01:26:26.390 --> 01:26:26.890
Thank you.

01:26:26.890 --> 01:26:28.440
- Thank you so much.

01:26:28.440 --> 01:26:29.910
This was fantastic.

01:26:29.910 --> 01:26:31.440
Thank you both.

01:26:31.440 --> 01:26:35.940
I do think end on
a more upbeat note.

01:26:35.940 --> 01:26:39.350
No more than we can
look simply to women,

01:26:39.350 --> 01:26:43.970
whether in our democracies
or around the world,

01:26:43.970 --> 01:26:45.920
to promote women's
rights, there's

01:26:45.920 --> 01:26:51.080
a big part of the equation
lies, of course, in the hands

01:26:51.080 --> 01:26:53.060
and the will of men.

01:26:53.060 --> 01:26:57.540
So too, I think, on the question
of multicultural citizenship,

01:26:57.540 --> 01:27:02.420
it would be unfair
and unwise to rely

01:27:02.420 --> 01:27:06.320
on the multiplicity of
cultures, and those people who

01:27:06.320 --> 01:27:10.640
are being denied or
subjected to injustice

01:27:10.640 --> 01:27:12.650
to look out for their
rights on their own.

01:27:12.650 --> 01:27:15.080
And fundamentally, I think
that's the point you just made.

01:27:15.080 --> 01:27:19.320
It's going to be incumbent on
the majority, and on people,

01:27:19.320 --> 01:27:22.670
again, who don't face the
same struggle to bring

01:27:22.670 --> 01:27:27.170
the kind of solidarity that true
citizenship, I think, entails.

01:27:27.170 --> 01:27:28.580
So thank you all.

01:27:28.580 --> 01:27:31.130
It's a pleasure,
and I urge everybody

01:27:31.130 --> 01:27:33.220
to come to this
unbelievable keynote

01:27:33.220 --> 01:27:35.000
reading and
conversation where we

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:38.510
have two of my favorite
writers on planet Earth,

01:27:38.510 --> 01:27:41.570
here at 2:00 PM, and then
the panel in the afternoon,

01:27:41.570 --> 01:27:44.256
The Gendered Politics
Of New Nationalism.

01:27:44.256 --> 01:27:45.880
So great afternoon
ahead for Radcliffe.

01:27:45.880 --> 01:27:47.730
Thank you.

